The article announces three appointments in the United States government. Paul K. Martin is appointed as the Inspector General of the United States Agency for International Development, replacing Ann Calvaresi Barr who resigned. Martin O'Malley is appointed as the Commissioner of Social Security for the remainder of the term until January 19, 2025, replacing Andrew M. Saul. Cardell Kenneth Richardson, Sr. is appointed as the Inspector General of the Department of State, replacing Steve A. Linick.